Deadfur: Well, sirry, the residue energy signature isn&#39;t Cybertronian
and almost perfectly matches the ones I know Minions share. I don&#39;t
know that specific one though, so I guess it&#39;s not someone&#39;s I know.
And my little McCorpse here actually died from being hit by a rock.
I&#39;m ready to bet that this said rock is particularly Minion smelling,
thus explaining the presence of the energy signature, unless a Minion
actually had weirder tastes than I do... which I strongly doubt. I
mean, I&#39;m unbeatable! Or at least I hope so.

He stopped blabbering for a moment, turned around, and took a good sniff.

Deadfur: Hey, sir, I also smell that energy signature coming from the
west. Good draft of wind too, so might be a meteor or something like
that. Has anything fallen recently?

